NAME: ABBE
FACTS: Director of Iena observatory. Author of a classical theory of microscopes in 1877 and of sinuses relations. Associated with Carl Zeiss. Conceiver of a refractometer and of the first apochromatic objectives and of orthoscopic eyepieces.
IAU_ORIGIN: Ernst Karl. German optician, physicist, astronomer (1840-1905).

NAME: ABUL WAFA
FACTS: Author of an arithmetrical treaty and of a precise method for sinuses calculations.
IAU_ORIGIN: Abū al-Wafā al-Būzajāni. Persian mathematician, astronomer (940-998).

NAME: AITKEN
FACTS: Author of New General Catalogue of Double Stars in 1932.

NAME: AL BIRUNI
FACTS: Great traveller. Astrologist of Rhazni Sultan in 1017. Civilizations historian. Author of Kitah al Qanun al Mas'udi, general astronomy treaty inpired from Ptolemeaus.
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the zone of librations.
IAU_ORIGIN: Abū ar-Rayhān Muhammad ibn Ahmad al-Birūnī. Persian astronomer, mathematician, geographer (973-1048).

NAME: ALDER
FACTS: Professor in Koln University in 1940. Nobel prize in 1950 with Otto Diels.
IAU_ORIGIN: Kurt. German organic chemist. Nobel laureate (1902-1958).

NAME: ALEKHIN
FACTS: Rockets designer.
IAU_ORIGIN: Nikolaj Pavlovich. Soviet rocket designer, engineer (1913-1964).

NAME: AL-KHWARIZMI
IAU_ORIGIN: Abū Ja'far Muhammad Ibn Mūsā. Iraqi mathematician (unkn-after 847).

NAME: AMICI
FACTS: Director of Florence observatory. Inventor of a specteoscope with prism. Survey on cristals orientation in minerals.

NAME: ANDERS
FACTS: Apollo 8 mission astronaut in december 1968 with Frank Borman and Jim Lovell.

NAME: ANDERSSON
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the zone of librations.

NAME: ANTONIADI
FACTS: Survey of planetary surfaces (Mars and Mercury principally) with 82 cm Meudon refractor. Opponant to Lowell theory of Mars channels.

NAME: ANUCHIN
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the zone of librations.

NAME: APOLLO
FACTS: Dedicated to Apollo american human missions that brought 12 astrnauts on the Moon surface.

NAME: APPLETON
FACTS: Assistant de Rutherford. Ministre de la recherche en 1939. Etude sur l'ionosphère. Auteur du premierécho radar sur la Lune en 1946.Prix Nobel en 1947. Rutherford assistant. Research Ministry in 1939. Surveys on atmosphere. Author of firdt radar echo on the Moon in 1946. Nobel laureate in 1947.
IAU_ORIGIN: Sir Edward Victor. British physicist. Nobel laureate (1892-1965).

NAME: ARMINSKI
IAU_ORIGIN: Franciszek. Polish astronomer (1789-1848). (Spelling changed from Armínski.)

NAME: ARRHENIUS
FACTS: Director of Stockholm university in 1897. Director of Nobel institute in 1905. Author of a theory of electrolytes ionization in 1887. Author of panspermia hypothesis in 1900 and of a cosmogonic theory. Chemistry Nobel laureate in 1903.
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the zone of librations.
IAU_ORIGIN: Svante August. Swedish chemist. Nobel laureate (1859-1927).

NAME: ARTAMONOV
FACTS: Scientist involved in the soviet space program.

NAME: ARTEM'EV
FACTS: Scientist involved in the soviet space program.

NAME: AVICENNA
NAMEDETAIL: Abu Ali Al Husayn Ibn Sina
FACTS: Doctor of prince Boukhara. Author of medecine cannons. Numerous deseases description and of their treatment. Author of a cosmology based on possible and necessary beings.
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the zone of librations.
IAU_ORIGIN: Abu Ali Al-Hussein Ibn Abdallah. Persian doctor (980-1037).

NAME: AVOGADRO
FACTS: Physics professor in Turino university in 1820. Discoverer of atoms number in an atom-gram. Author of  a law on gases density.

NAME: BABAKIN
FACTS: Scientist involved in the soviet space program.

NAME: BABCOCK
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the zone of librations.

NAME: BACKLUND
FACTS: Director of Pulkovo observatory in 1895. Survey of celestial mechanic.
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the librations zone

NAME: BARBIER
FACTS: Survey on stellar spectrophotometry. Star spectral classification with D. Chalonge. International observation network of atmosphere luminescence.

NAME: BARRINGER
FACTS: Survey on Meteor Crater in Arizona. Author of meteoritic origin of lunar craters.

NAME: BECQUEREL
FACTS: Discoverer of piezoelectricity in 1819 and of a photovoltaic battery in 1839. Conceiver of the electrochimic actinometer.

NAME: BECVAR
FACTS: Author of several celestial and stellar atlases.

NAME: BELL
FACTS: Inventor of the telephone in 1876.
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the zone of librations.

NAME: BELYAEV
FACTS: Voskhod 2 mission cosmonaut with Leonov on the march 18 1965.

NAME: BERGMAN
FACTS: Mineralogist. Discoverer of nickel, wolfram and of carbonates composition.
IAU_ORIGIN: Torbern Olof. Swedish chemist, mineralogist, astronomer (1735-1784).

NAME: BERGSTRAND
FACTS:
